1/(n+1)
{\rm E}[Z] = \int_{z=0}^\infty (1-F_Z(z)) \, dz = \int_{z=0}^1 (1 - z^n) \, dz= \frac{n}{n+1},
{\rm E}[Y] = \int_{y=0}^\infty (1 - F_Y(y)) \, dy = \int_{y=0}^1 (1-y)^n \, dy = \frac{1}{n+1}.
f_Z(x)=nx^{n-1}
EZ=\int_0^1 x nx^{n-1}dx=n\int_0^1x^ndx=n\left(\frac{x^{n+1}}{n+1}|_0^1\right)=\frac{n}{n+1}
f_Y(x)=n(1-x)^{n-1}
EY=\int_0^1 x n(1-x)^{n-1}dx=n\int_0^1x(1-x)^{n-1}dx
=-\int_0^1xd(1-x)^{n}=-x(1-x)^n|_0^1+\int_0^1(1-x)^ndx=-\int_0^1(1-x)^nd(1-x)
=-\frac{(1-x)^{n+1}}{n+1}|_0^1=\frac{1}{n+1}
